37
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:36,690
Oh right. Add in a "pii."

38
00:03:36,690 --> 00:03:39,430
Okay, I'll add a "pii."

39
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:41,080
So [censor beep]-san.

40
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,840
Not [censor beep]! It's Katsura!

41
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,670
Oh, well...never mind.

42
00:03:46,270 --> 00:03:50,880
Oh, but we'll distort your face, so your identity won't be revealed.

43
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:56,110
Distort?! What? Is my face distorted right now?!

44
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:58,350
Yes, is that a problem?

45
00:03:58,350 --> 00:04:02,630
Remove it right now! Doing such an obscene thing to a person's face is unacceptable!

46
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:05,460
No, but we're just being cautious for your sake...

47
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:07,540
Don't do me any favors!

48
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:13,230
Besides, it's more of a problem if people think my face goes against what is considered good taste.

49
00:04:13,730 --> 00:04:16,740
Remove it immediately! Who do you think I am?!

50
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:18,210
Oh but...

51
00:04:18,210 --> 00:04:22,340
I am a master of disguise. I am under disguise right now.

52
00:04:22,340 --> 00:04:27,250
I am nicknamed "Getaway Kotaro." As if I would reveal my true self so easily.

53
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:30,580
Oh, but you've already revealed your real first and last name.

54
00:04:30,790 --> 00:04:34,130
A woman should not speak of "revealing" herself.

55
00:04:34,130 --> 00:04:36,350
Well, I don't quite understand...

56
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:37,930
But never mind.

57
00:04:37,930 --> 00:04:40,480
I'm sorry. Anyway, we'll remove the distortion on your face.

58
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:48,200
Umm... let me return to my questions. K-san, I mean Katsura-san...

59
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:53,500
Why did you agree to this close-up interview today?

60
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:54,610
Well...

61
00:04:54,610 --> 00:04:58,840
First of all, I want people to understand what the Anti-Foreigner Faction stands for.

62
00:04:59,350 --> 00:05:02,410
Many people are afraid of us because we have been labeled as

63
00:05:02,410 --> 00:05:06,640
criminals, terrorists, and guerillas...as dangerous men.

64
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:09,470
Most people in society do believe that.

65
00:05:09,470 --> 00:05:11,120
However, that is wrong.

66
00:05:11,470 --> 00:05:15,540
It's true that there are robbers and bandits.

67
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:16,630
Enjoy.

68
00:05:16,630 --> 00:05:18,150
Thank you.

69
00:05:18,150 --> 00:05:20,170
However, that's just a small segment.

70
00:05:21,270 --> 00:05:23,740
Most of us love this nation and want to change it.

71
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:28,810
We want people to understand that we are loyal patriots.

72
00:05:28,810 --> 00:05:29,930
...I see.

73
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,610
Secondly...

74
00:05:35,450 --> 00:05:38,880
Secondly... Huh?

75
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,680
It's hard to eat with this on!

76
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:41,550
The moustache gets in the way!

77
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:42,760
K-Katsura-san!

78
00:05:43,170 --> 00:05:48,930
[Note: Literally, she says "marumie" or "open to view." But Katsura puts a sexual spin on it.]

79
00:05:43,170 --> 00:05:45,830
Your...face is in plain view! ...

80
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:48,930
A woman shouldn't speak about anything being in plain view!

81
00:05:48,930 --> 00:05:50,320
I didn't mean it like that!

82
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:54,730
Ikumatsu-dono, what is the meaning of ramen noodles during an interview? Are you...

83
00:05:54,730 --> 00:05:58,220
We're a ramen shop. If you want tea, go to a teashop.

84
00:05:58,220 --> 00:06:01,160
Geez, bringing a whole brigade in here...!

85
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,850
She scolded me.

86
00:06:02,850 --> 00:06:06,260
No, never mind that. But your face is in plain view.

87
00:06:06,260 --> 00:06:08,750
Don't use that phrase!

88
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:10,780
Look, never mind that already.

89
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,580
Hmm... Where were we?

90
00:06:13,580 --> 00:06:17,280
Yes... you were answering my question about why you agreed to our interview.

91
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:19,190
You were on the second reason.

92
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:20,050
Oh, yes, yes.

93
00:06:22,450 --> 00:06:25,640
The second reason. Well, the second reason is...

94
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:27,530
Huh?

95
00:06:31,030 --> 00:06:33,010
There's no second reason. Just one will do.

96
00:06:33,010 --> 00:06:36,880
This aroma is richer than before... Delicious...

97
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,780
Oh, I see...

98
00:06:40,210 --> 00:06:45,220
Well then, you wanted to broadcast the mission of the Anti-Foreigner Faction to everyone watching.

99
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:50,960
And you want each viewer to ponder about what can be done for this country.

100
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,640
Am I correct?

101
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,160
Oh yes, that's it.

102
00:06:55,630 --> 00:06:57,110
That's just what I wanted to say.

103
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:59,580
What kind of stock did she use?

104
00:06:59,580 --> 00:07:01,400
Flying fish? Dried mackerel?

105
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:05,300
Excuse me! Please don't "shoot from the hip" like that that.

106
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:09,150
[Note: She literally says, "koshi o oru" which means bend your hips, but Katsura takes it sexually.]

107
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:09,150
Don't use uncouth phrases like "massage the hip"!

108
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:10,980
He totally misunderstood.

109
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:14,010
Rather, that's an old lecher's gag line.

110
00:07:14,190 --> 00:07:18,230
Right. Even when you are in the midst of a secret mission,

111
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:21,620
you must not forget hidden meanings and flavors.

112
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:24,680
Yes. So may I go on to the next question?

113
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:27,020
Like your daily schedule.

114
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:29,680
Elizabeth!

115
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,960
What's wrong? What happened?!

116
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:36,260
What is happening?! A strange creature has crashed into our interview site!

117
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:38,560
That's no strange creature! That's Elizabeth!

118
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,110
Katsura!

119
00:07:40,610 --> 00:07:42,840
Your number is up today!

120
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:45,790
I-It's the Shinsengumi! What is going on?!

121
00:07:45,790 --> 00:07:48,480
They knew where the interview was taking place!

122
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:50,440
Die! Katsura!!

123
00:07:58,110 --> 00:08:01,420
And in this manner, a hectic day begins.

124
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:05,140
It's about time I left...

125
00:08:03,730 --> 00:08:07,500
[Note: She is dressed as Eligo 13, a spoof of Golgo 13]

126
00:08:03,730 --> 00:08:07,500
[Revival]

127
00:08:05,140 --> 00:08:07,500
Huh? Is this part of the schedule?

128
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:11,960
Of course! Can the cameraman follow?

129
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,500
I don't want to block his way.

130
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,760
Katsura!

131
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:17,640
Hey! What's the big idea crashing my place like this?!

132
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,260
Oh, sorry.

133
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:22,920
Katsura-san, you seem to be accustomed to this crazy situation.

134
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:25,300
Does this happen a lot?

135
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:29,880
Well, yes. Those guys always show up anytime, anyplace.

136
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:32,480
Especially during mealtimes and when I'm asleep.

137
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:35,730
When most people tend to be off their guard.

138
00:08:35,730 --> 00:08:37,210
Exactly.

139
00:08:37,210 --> 00:08:41,710
They think I'm defenseless, but in three years, they have never been successful.

140
00:08:41,710 --> 00:08:44,360
They can attack at mealtimes if they like...

141
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:46,600
Because I have Tasty Stick snacks on me at all times.

142
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,210
This one's corn potage.

143
00:08:48,380 --> 00:08:51,580
I love them, too. The corn potage-flavored ones.

144
00:08:52,460 --> 00:08:55,820
I love the rich flavor as it goes down my throat.

145
00:08:55,820 --> 00:08:57,370
But the only disappointment

146
00:08:57,370 --> 00:09:01,810
is that it often disintegrates into powder because I hold on to it for so long.

147
00:09:02,210 --> 00:09:06,060
I see... After all, your work is very dangerous.

148
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:10,790
I'm fully aware of that. Every man from the moment he is born,

149
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:14,030
must live life prepared to die.

150
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:19,900
[If you are always prepared, you can remain calm. No matter what happens, there is no fear.]

151
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:17,140
If you are always prepared, you can remain calm.

152
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:19,900
No matter what happens, there is no fear.

153
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:24,750
To be honest, I've never known fear ever since I was born.

154
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:26,640
Now then, I'm going to escape from here.

155
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:28,540
Katsura!!

156
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:39,760
Katsura-san, didn't you just yelp?

157
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:44,530
That was a battle cry! You mistook it for "Uryahh!"

158
00:09:44,530 --> 00:09:46,520
No, you were scared just now.

159
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:48,670
What? From over there, too?!

160
00:09:50,270 --> 00:09:53,120
Tasty Stick! Corn Potage!

161
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:53,870
[Corn Potage]

162
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,930
We managed to escape.

163
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:02,150
Well, this is my morning warm-up.

164
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:06,490
It's a morning filled with heroism. Truly like an Anti-Foreigner patriot.

165
00:10:06,490 --> 00:10:10,050
Umm... Katsura-san, aren't you getting off the roof?

166
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:11,440
No, I'm not.

167
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:17,310
When you're a big name like me, you get recognized immediately on the streets.

168
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:20,420
Katsura-san, you said you were a master of disguise.

169
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:23,150
Does that mean it hasn't been working?

170
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:23,980
Look.

171
00:10:23,980 --> 00:10:25,600
Katsura-san, are you ignoring me?

172
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:29,710
There are others besides us who walk on rooftops.

173
00:10:29,710 --> 00:10:31,510
They too are Anti-Foreigner patriots.

174
00:10:31,510 --> 00:10:33,710
What? Are you serious, Katsura-san?

175
00:10:33,710 --> 00:10:34,600
Yes.

176
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,920
Hey! Good morning.

177
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:45,110
Katsura-san, they're ignoring you. They're obviously just carpenters.

178
00:10:46,150 --> 00:10:49,630
That's Gosaku. He must've had a fight with his wife again.

179
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:52,470
Look, the first half is about to end!

180
00:10:52,470 --> 00:10:55,420
And you haven't done anything that an Anti-Foreigner patriot would do!

181
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:59,370
Real political activism... The Anti-Foreigner movement...

182
00:10:59,370 --> 00:11:01,680
is a series of subtle, unperceivable acts.

183
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,560
Wow! He seems to be making some sensible statements

184
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:06,370
and trying to connect them to these confusing events!

185
00:11:06,370 --> 00:11:09,760
Stay tuned! Don't change that channel.

186
00:11:08,980 --> 00:11:12,750
[Don't change that channel!!]

187
