[THE EDO]
[The Dawning of Japan Special The Unstoppable - One day undercover]

188
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:16,190
Sorry, I'm late.

189
00:11:16,190 --> 00:11:19,710
Katsura-san! Elizabeth-san! Good morning!

190
00:11:19,710 --> 00:11:23,170
We have cameras here today, but don't worry about them.

191
00:11:23,170 --> 00:11:24,850
We'll distort all your faces.

192
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:26,270
Right!

193
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:28,230
This has never been made public before.

194
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:30,160
It's the secret meeting place of the Anti-Foreigner Faction.

195
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,770
This is the first time people other than our comrades have been inside.

196
00:11:32,770 --> 00:11:35,290
That battle strategy couldn't be helped!

197
00:11:35,290 --> 00:11:38,440
And that's why you'll accept it?! What a masochistic viewpoint!

198
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:40,760
What do you do here, Katsura-san?

199
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:43,900
Anti-Foreigner Faction members mainly exchange information.

200
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:46,960
They're reporting on the results of their actions.

201
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,310
And the refreshment during these times...

202
00:11:49,310 --> 00:11:50,990
is salami-flavored Tasty Stick .

203
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:55,260
Salami flavor? I like that too.

204
00:11:55,260 --> 00:11:58,790
In other words, what we do most of the time as Anti-Foreigner Faction members

205
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:02,240
is exchange information.

206
00:12:02,650 --> 00:12:05,710
All kinds of data that we've gathered from our travels here and there.

207
00:12:05,710 --> 00:12:09,850
Mostly the state of the universe and classified news of the Bakufu government.

208
00:12:09,850 --> 00:12:13,370
We exchange them and slowly spread them.

209
00:12:13,370 --> 00:12:17,270
Namely, we exchange ideas and viewpoints with those in higher positions and try to persuade them.

210
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:20,200
And then, we force change from within the nation.

211
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,920
Masochistic?!

212
00:12:22,130 --> 00:12:24,110
That's just Otsu-dono's sales strategy!

213
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:28,080
No! Otsu-dono has clearly stated that she is seeing Goemon.

214
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:31,060
In entertainment jargon, seeing equals you-know-what.

215
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:33,800
Why you...! And you call yourself a member of the Otsu Fan Club?!

216
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:34,530
I'll tell the president about you!

217
00:12:34,530 --> 00:12:38,190
Well, I've switched to Tama-dono! I'm a rebel without a cause!

218
00:12:38,190 --> 00:12:39,400
I'll punish you for that! Stay right there!

219
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:41,860
No way! You're the one who should admit the two are seeing each other!

220
00:12:41,860 --> 00:12:47,440
What?! Otsu-dono is being fooled! That's why I refuse to admit it!

221
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:50,750
Get real! It makes no difference if she's being fooled with money or violence!

222
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:52,130
Silence! Silence! Silence!

223
00:12:52,130 --> 00:12:55,850
You're no better than a natto-flavored Tasty Stick!

224
00:12:52,130 --> 00:12:55,850
[Note: Natto = fermented soy beans]

225
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:57,640
And what's wrong with natto-flavored sticks?!

226
00:12:56,120 --> 00:13:00,020
[Stop fighting.]

227
00:12:57,640 --> 00:13:00,020
It's untouched, but always number one in popularity!

228
00:13:00,020 --> 00:13:02,030
And besides, what about you with your salad-flavored sticks?!

229
00:13:02,190 --> 00:13:05,300
Katsura-san, are they really discussing the state of the universe?

230
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:07,360
I heard names that usually appear in entertainment gossip columns.

231
00:13:08,620 --> 00:13:13,830
Well, the exchange of information is usually done in secret code.

232
00:13:13,830 --> 00:13:18,130
And depending on the passion one feels, there may be a confrontation.

233
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:19,450
I see.

234
00:13:19,450 --> 00:13:20,310
Still...

235
00:13:20,380 --> 00:13:22,930
Cut it out already, you punks!

236
00:13:22,930 --> 00:13:27,010
K-Katsura-san... We're sorry.

237
00:13:27,010 --> 00:13:30,420
That's why he's Katsura-san, The Unstoppable!

238
00:13:30,420 --> 00:13:32,990
Only a few words uttered and the ronin...

239
00:13:32,990 --> 00:13:35,210
I like Goemon quite a bit!

240
00:13:35,210 --> 00:13:40,530
He's the embodiment of the unsightliness of the entertainment world and he's refreshing!

241
00:13:40,530 --> 00:13:41,270
Huh?

242
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:43,390
Katsura!!

243
00:13:43,430 --> 00:13:44,070
[It's the Shinsengumi!!]

244
00:13:44,330 --> 00:13:46,670
Tasty Stick, salami!

245
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:51,070
Katsura-san, not again!

246
00:13:51,070 --> 00:13:53,690
And that's how the meetings usually end.

247
00:13:53,690 --> 00:13:55,040
Just the way it was scheduled, huh?

248
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:58,330
Katsura-san, just how many times a day are you attacked?

249
00:13:58,330 --> 00:14:02,890
Every time I get to the meeting hall, they attack.

250
00:14:02,890 --> 00:14:07,890
As a result, I can't exchange data properly! They're such a pain!

251
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:12,130
You're the worst pain! You're just being followed!

252
00:14:12,130 --> 00:14:15,130
You brought those guys from this morning!

253
00:14:15,130 --> 00:14:18,700
Gosaku! Get away quickly! They're here!

254
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:21,010
I said, that's not Gosaku.

255
00:14:21,010 --> 00:14:22,360
Katsura!!

256
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:31,670
We got away somehow. I'm really exhausted.

257
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:33,400
The real thing is just starting.

258
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:36,190
Well, I don't care whether it's the real take or not.

259
00:14:36,190 --> 00:14:40,700
Next, I shall show you how we meet with an important personage and persuade him.

260
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:44,470
Important personage? Who is he?!

261
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,600
Someone we cannot do without.

262
00:14:55,370 --> 00:14:56,830
Is he out?

263
00:14:56,830 --> 00:14:59,780
No, that can't be. He's got to be here.

264
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:04,090
He's not home, after all.

265
00:15:04,090 --> 00:15:05,720
No, he's here.

266
00:15:07,530 --> 00:15:08,890
Katsura-san, um...

267
00:15:08,890 --> 00:15:10,010
No, he's here!

268
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:15,090
I said I don't have the rent!

269
00:15:15,090 --> 00:15:16,560
Katsura-san!!

270
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:20,760
Gintoki, you will say "yes" today.

271
00:15:20,970 --> 00:15:23,900
Damn, the door came off.

272
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:26,500
You are destined to fight alongside me.

273
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:30,250
Let us change this rotten world together!

274
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:33,740
This part is hard to reattach.

275
00:15:33,740 --> 00:15:35,610
Oh... I admit this is not a simple request.

276
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:37,430
This will do.

277
00:15:37,430 --> 00:15:39,750
But it's possible with you and I.

278
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:41,120
Gintoki, where are you going?!

279
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:43,270
Katsura-san, how is it going?

280
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:47,090
Yes, I'm getting a favorable impression. But it'll all depend on my final push.

281
00:15:47,970 --> 00:15:52,960
Announcer Hanano, can you reach into my pocket for me? It's my trump card.

282
00:15:53,380 --> 00:15:57,410
In a wager, the one who shows his hand first is the loser.

283
00:15:57,410 --> 00:16:01,310
The one who hides his trump card until the last moment is the winner.

284
00:16:02,110 --> 00:16:03,770
Oh, that's it.

285
00:16:03,770 --> 00:16:08,240
In truth, the Tasty Stick flavors vary greatly according to size.

286
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:10,680
For example, the smallest is the chocolate-flavored one.

287
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:16,020
Gintoki... I wonder if he'll act the same when he sees this.

288
00:16:16,770 --> 00:16:17,750
Katsura-san,

289
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:20,640
the chocolate-flavored Tasty Stick that was your trump card has been nabbed.

290
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:21,490
What?!

291
00:16:21,490 --> 00:16:22,940
By whom?!

292
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:24,320
Ouch!

293
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:26,380
Oh, hello, Katsura-san.

294
00:16:26,380 --> 00:16:27,920
Oh, hello.

295
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:30,890
Oh no... There's no need for tea.

296
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:35,720
No. Huh? Really? Thanks. Please don't bother.

297
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:37,910
What exactly are you doing here?!

298
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:39,210
Katsura!!

299
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,910
Surrender nice and easy.

300
00:16:40,910 --> 00:16:42,620
Ngoh! They're here again!

301
00:16:42,620 --> 00:16:45,680
Hey, girls are not supposed say "Ngoh."

302
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:48,550
Shut up! This isn't the time for that!

303
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:50,350
Katsura-san! Hurry, hurry!

304
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:53,890
Don't pull me out. It'll leave a hole and Gintoki will scold me.

305
00:16:53,890 --> 00:16:55,260
Do you...intend to...

306
00:16:55,260 --> 00:16:58,030
live here...forever...?!

307
00:16:58,030 --> 00:16:59,060
Oh, I'm out.

308
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:05,840
[Go up!]

309
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:06,850
All right.

310
00:17:09,810 --> 00:17:11,670
Up above! He's running away up there!

311
00:17:11,670 --> 00:17:13,850
Capture him! Don't let him get away!

312
00:17:13,850 --> 00:17:16,340
Announcer Hanano, after this,

313
00:17:16,340 --> 00:17:19,580
shall we go to a certain place I know to eat,

314
00:17:19,790 --> 00:17:21,860
drink and look at some old photos...

315
00:17:21,860 --> 00:17:24,230
and welcome a surprise guest,

316
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:27,440
and finally, read a poignant letter from an old friend?

317
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:33,430
[Spoof of "Uchi Kuru?!" COME TO MY "HOME SWEET HOME" a TV show that visits a celebrity's hometown.]

318
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:31,060
How about something touching like that?

319
00:17:31,060 --> 00:17:33,430
What are you talking about?!

320
00:17:33,430 --> 00:17:35,530
Do you want a letter?

321
00:17:35,530 --> 00:17:37,000
You may be popular now, but long ago,

322
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,540
maybe you were a wimp who was always teased for looking like a girl.

323
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:43,490
Or a teacher from grade school said some embarrassing things about you!!

324
00:17:43,490 --> 00:17:45,890
Is that what you want?!

325
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:51,620
Don't tell me you don't have a letter?

326
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:56,120
Of course not! We're not interested in any of your friends!

327
00:17:57,020 --> 00:18:00,250
I figured as much and already have one ready.

328
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:04,270
Just how prepared are you?! Just how much is according to your plans?!

329
00:18:04,270 --> 00:18:06,830
Wait for the right moment, then present it. It will be a touching scene.

330
00:18:06,830 --> 00:18:09,440
I'm counting on you. It took me all night to write it!!

331
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:13,220
You wrote it?! That's enough to make me cry!

332
00:18:14,780 --> 00:18:15,910
Eat this!!

333
00:18:17,150 --> 00:18:20,780
In order to get ratings, a little bit of faking is necessary.

334
00:18:20,780 --> 00:18:22,810
That's not the point!

335
00:18:27,770 --> 00:18:31,620
Where is the boundary between "the real" and "the fake"?

336
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:34,620
I want everyone in mass media to ask themselves that!

337
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:37,290
What?! Are you judging the mass media?!

338
00:18:37,290 --> 00:18:39,360
Huh? Katsura-san, can you see that up ahead?!

339
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:41,350
Up front!! Up ahead! Ahead!

340
00:18:43,790 --> 00:18:46,700
Make sure you get this on camera!

341
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:48,810
This is how an Anti-Foreigner patriot lives!

342
00:18:48,810 --> 00:18:51,290
I've been nervous about that for a while.

343
00:18:51,290 --> 00:18:53,710
Careful! That camera is really old!

344
00:18:55,510 --> 00:18:59,430
Hey, cameraman! Did you get my jump just now?

345
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:01,340
It was better than Jackie himself!

346
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:02,790
[Note: He's referring to Jackie Chan.]

347
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:02,790
Got it all, Katsura-san!

348
00:19:03,650 --> 00:19:05,230
Good.

349
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,470
Where am I?!

350
00:19:18,660 --> 00:19:20,530
Huh? You just noticed?

351
00:19:20,530 --> 00:19:23,730
We're in the middle of shooting an action scene that surpasses even Jackie's!

352
00:19:23,730 --> 00:19:26,410
What do you mean? I don't understand!

353
00:19:26,410 --> 00:19:31,520
Propaganda must be convincing and have images full of power and intensity!

354
00:19:31,520 --> 00:19:34,690
By the way, can you make me a copy of this later? I'm going to send it back home.

355
00:19:34,690 --> 00:19:36,850
Back home? You're gonna send it back?!

356
00:19:38,170 --> 00:19:39,610
Katsura...

357
00:19:39,610 --> 00:19:41,830
It's time to say your prayers.

358
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:51,770
Don't panic. I'm The Unstoppable.

359
00:19:51,770 --> 00:19:54,120
They'll be more afraid of me and miss.

360
00:20:00,610 --> 00:20:04,600
Announcer Hanano, make sure you tell the people of this nation

361
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,050
what kind of people we Anti-Foreigner patriots were!

362
00:20:07,050 --> 00:20:08,190
Katsura-san?!

363
00:20:08,660 --> 00:20:10,190
I'm counting on you.

364
00:20:15,740 --> 00:20:17,730
So long, Katsura.

365
00:20:20,930 --> 00:20:23,030
Katsura-san!!

366
00:20:31,580 --> 00:20:32,810
Huh? Huh?!

367
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:36,500
If you are always prepared, you can remain calm.

368
00:20:37,210 --> 00:20:40,340
No matter what happens, there is nothing to fear!

369
00:20:41,170 --> 00:20:42,350
Katsura-san...

370
00:20:43,970 --> 00:20:47,630
Okita-san! It's going to take a while to recharge!

371
00:20:47,630 --> 00:20:49,310
Damn it! Let's go!

372
00:20:49,310 --> 00:20:50,750
Look!

373
00:20:52,370 --> 00:20:53,970
Bye bee!

374
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,570
[Bye bee]

375
00:20:58,160 --> 00:20:59,870
No way!

376
00:20:59,870 --> 00:21:02,110
He's dangerous! He's so outdated! He's too outdated!

377
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:10,990
Hey! You there, woman! Don't move!

378
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:13,490
You're one of Katsura's friends.

379
00:21:13,490 --> 00:21:15,350
No, I'm just reporting...

380
00:21:15,350 --> 00:21:19,210
Don't lie. You're coming with me for questioning!

381
00:21:19,210 --> 00:21:20,090
No!

382
00:21:20,860 --> 00:21:22,400
What's this?

383
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,630
To everyone in the Shinsengumi...

384
00:21:26,630 --> 00:21:29,720
I know it's odd to ask this of an enemy,

385
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:32,900
but please don't lay a hand on the woman in front of you.

386
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:39,310
She is simply a journalist and I made her come do a story on me.

387
00:21:39,310 --> 00:21:42,010
She has nothing to do with the Anti-Foreigner Faction.

388
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:47,280
You are my enemy, but as a man who also wishes for the happiness of the people of Edo,

389
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:51,790
as a samurai who lives for truth... I want to believe in you all.

390
00:21:52,790 --> 00:21:56,180
To Announcer Hanano and her two-man crew,

391
00:21:56,180 --> 00:22:02,550
I admire you all for putting yourselves in harm's way in order to report the truth.

392
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:04,150
And while we both work in different ways,

393
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:07,400
you too, are patriots who desire peace in Edo.

394
00:22:08,050 --> 00:22:10,140
We are comrades.

395
00:22:10,140 --> 00:22:14,420
Please continue your endeavors. I will be watching every day.

396
00:22:14,420 --> 00:22:15,780
Kotaro Katsura.

397
00:22:18,770 --> 00:22:19,950
P.S.!

398
00:22:20,540 --> 00:22:23,170
Okita-san? What's this ticking sound?

399
00:22:23,170 --> 00:22:24,950
What is this?

400
00:22:24,950 --> 00:22:27,990
All Shinsengumi should die!

401
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:35,720
The thing to look for is the long hair. This messy long hair.

402
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:39,050
He always has Tasty Sticks on hand

403
00:22:39,050 --> 00:22:41,980
to use as trump cards and his sense of humor is totally outdated.

404
00:22:41,980 --> 00:22:44,580
You'll get sick just talking to him for a minute.

405
00:22:44,580 --> 00:22:46,360
If you see this face,

406
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:48,210
please call the police immediately.

407
00:22:48,210 --> 00:22:51,220
Go to hell, Katsura!!

408
00:24:24,740 --> 00:24:29,750
["Rhinoceros Beetles Teach Boys That Life is Precious"]

409
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:28,820
The next episode! Beetle hunting!

410
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:34,450
[The Odd Jobs Trio find out that rhinoceros beetles can be sold at high prices and set out to catch them!!]

411
00:24:34,450 --> 00:24:39,690
[But when they get to the forest, the Shinsengumi is already hard at work.]

412
01:16:43,700 --> 01:17:04,000
[Salami]
